sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant MutWH as Mutating Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant ValWH as Validating Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Controller as RayCluster Controller
    participant OAuthProxy as oauth-proxy sidecar<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant RayDash as Ray Dashboard<br/>8265/TCP HTTP
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over User,Router: Flow 1: RayCluster Creation (OpenShift)

    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl create RayCluster<br/>HTTPS/6443, Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>MutWH: POST /mutate-ray-io-v1-raycluster<br/>HTTPS/9443, API Server mTLS
    MutWH-->>K8sAPI: Inject oauth-proxy sidecar +<br/>mTLS init container (create-cert)
    K8sAPI->>ValWH: POST /validate-ray-io-v1-raycluster<br/>HTTPS/9443, API Server mTLS
    ValWH-->>K8sAPI: Validated OK

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Route, Service, SA,<br/>CRB, Secret, NetworkPolicy<br/>HTTPS/6443, SA Token

    Note over User,Router: Flow 2: Dashboard Access

    User->>Router: GET https://ray-dashboard-{cluster}...<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS
    Router->>OAuthProxy: Reencrypt TLS/8443
    OAuthProxy->>K8sAPI: OAuth delegation check<br/>HTTPS/443
    K8sAPI-->>OAuthProxy: Auth OK
    OAuthProxy->>RayDash: HTTP/8265 (localhost, plaintext)
    RayDash-->>OAuthProxy: Dashboard HTML
    OAuthProxy-->>Router: HTTPS Response
    Router-->>User: Dashboard

    Note over User,Router: Flow 3: mTLS Certificate Provisioning

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create CA Secret<br/>(RSA 2048-bit, 1yr validity)<br/>HTTPS/6443, SA Token
    Note over Controller: Init container (create-cert)<br/>generates per-pod certs<br/>signed by cluster CA

    Note over User,Router: Flow 4: AppWrapper Scheduling

    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl create AppWrapper<br/>HTTPS/6443, Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>MutWH: POST /mutate-...appwrapper<br/>HTTPS/9443
    MutWH-->>K8sAPI: Defaults applied
    K8sAPI->>ValWH: POST /validate-...appwrapper<br/>HTTPS/9443
    ValWH->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>HTTPS/6443
    K8sAPI-->>ValWH: Access OK
    ValWH-->>K8sAPI: Validated

    Note over Controller: AppWrapper Controller<br/>creates Kueue Workload,<br/>then creates wrapped resources<br/>when quota admitted
